ee9823ab-c3e8-4a14-b998-8c22ec246bd3.title: Scalable Vector Graphics
ee9823ab-c3e8-4a14-b998-8c22ec246bd3.content: Scalable Vector Graphics (SVG) is an Extensible Markup Language (XML)-based vector image format for two-dimensional graphics with support for interactivity and animation. The SVG specification is an open standard developed by the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) since 1999.

fdf00227-084f-48bc-a450-9242a0963f1f.title: Open standard
fdf00227-084f-48bc-a450-9242a0963f1f.content: An open standard is a standard that is publicly available and has various rights to use associated with it and may also have various properties of how it was designed (e.g. open process). There is no single definition, and interpretations vary with usage.
